        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-25T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-25T12:00:00-05:00" n="655" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d655">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/6–2545: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 655 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">most immediate</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-25T19:00:00+02:00">June 25, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3826. <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName> agrees entirely that a
                    decision should be reached at earliest possible moment as to where Tangier
                    conversations are to be held. (Your 2909, June 23<note n="1" xml:id="d655fn1">
                        <ref target="#d654">Document No. 654</ref>.</note>) He alleges that he
                    receives practically no communications of importance from Brit Govt at this
                    juncture. “<persName corresp="#p_CMWS1">Churchill</persName>” he added “is too
                    busy electioneering and trying to kick us out of the Levant”.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName> insists that French will not go to
                    London to discuss Tangier (<gloss target="#t_rptd1">rptd</gloss> London 464;
                    sent <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> 3826).</p>
                <p>He agrees that USSR should be informed as suggested by <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> and that govt of country where conversations are to be held
                    might properly take initiative in that respect.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
